Package: Rbot
Version: 1.0.1
Date: 2018-08-07
Type: Package
Title: Send Messages and Execute Functions in R from your Cellphone using the Telegram App
Authors@R: person("Nico", "Katzke", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "nfkatzke@gmail.com")
Description: Send messages from R to your phone, as well as execute functions in R
    using the powerful Telegram app. This package functions as a wrapper to simplify
    using telegram.bot and telegram packages in R, while also providing a platform 
    for executing functions in scripts.
Maintainer: Nico Katzke <nfkatzke@gmail.com>
BugReports: https://github.com/nicktz/Rbot/issues
URL: https://rbot.nfkatzke.com/
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports:
    telegram,
    telegram.bot,
    purrr,
    glue
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Repository: CRAN
NeedsCompilation: yes
ByteCompile: yes
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown
